<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="550" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,330,1041]" pageId="29" pageNumber="550">
COMMENTS: Collected on the same day as the type of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1850" box="[799,998,799,825]" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Alauda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciolata">
<emphasis box="[799,998,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="550">Alauda fasciolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see above). The type locality is probably just south of Potchefstroom. Since this name was shown to be a homonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Latham, 1801)" baseAuthorityName="Latham" baseAuthorityYear="1801" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Zosterops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lateralis">
<emphasis box="[1113,1325,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="550">Zosterops lateralis</emphasis>
(Latham, 1801)
</taxonomicName>
, a species from 
<collectingCountry box="[402,505,871,897]" name="Australia" pageId="29" pageNumber="550">Australia</collectingCountry>
and neighboring islands, Hartlaub created a substitute name, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hartlaub 1865: 8 - 9)" baseAuthorityName="Hartlaub" baseAuthorityPageNumber="8 - 9" baseAuthorityYear="1865" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Zosterops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sundevalli">
<emphasis box="[1204,1436,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="550">Zosterops sundevalli</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hartlaub, G." box="[159,386,906,933]" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" pagination="1 - 30" refId="ref28842" refString="Hartlaub, G. (1865) Monographischer Versuch uber die Gattung Zosterops. Journal fur Ornithologie, 13 (73), 1 - 30. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 02261150" type="journal article" year="1865">Hartlaub 1865: 8–9</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. NRM 568713 is also the 
<typeStatus box="[699,802,907,933]" pageId="29" pageNumber="550">lectotype</typeStatus>
for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hartlaub" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[853,1086,907,933]" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Zosterops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sundevalli">
<emphasis box="[853,1086,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="550">Zosterops sundevalli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Swainson, 1838" authorityName="Swainson" authorityYear="1838" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Zosterops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pallidus">
<emphasis box="[1102,1311,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="550">Zosterops pallidus</emphasis>
Swainson, 1838
</taxonomicName>
, based on “Dr. Burchell’s Coll. No. 43”, collected on the north bank of the Orange River, about 
<quantity box="[1285,1356,943,969]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" unit="km" value="16.0">16 km</quantity>
east of Prieska on 
<date box="[277,427,979,1005]" pageId="29" pageNumber="550" value="1811-09-18">18 Sept 1811</date>
, has priority over both names. The type specimen is in the Oxford University Museum of Natural History.
</paragraph>
